    { "type": "QuestionDoor", "id": "d1", "x":  6, "y":  6, "text": "SD = sqrt(2) approx 1.414", "correct": true },
    { "type": "QuestionDoor", "id": "d2", "x": 16, "y":  6, "text": "SD = sigma1 - sigma2 = -2", "correct": false, "reflection": "SDs are never negative, and you do NOT subtract SDs. You add the VARIANCES (sigma^2/n) and take the square root: sqrt(36/36 + 64/64) = sqrt(2)." },
